 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  The sign for "here"
  <br/>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   Main version:
   <b>
    HERE
   </b>
   <br/>
   <img border="0" src="/images/here.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   <iframe allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2dALbgMQWmk?rel=0" width="560">
   </iframe>
   <br/>
   <br/>
   <b>
    Handshape
   </b>
   : Both hands are in a relaxed flat hand shape..  By
  "relaxed" I mean the fingers can be together, or they can be loosely
  separated.  The hands are not "rigidly" flat, but have a very
  slight curve.  The thumbs are open a little bit, but certainly not
  "extended."
   <br/>
   <b>
    Location
   </b>
   :  Out in front of you, about belly height.
   <br/>
   <b>
    Orientation
   </b>
   : palms facing up
   <br/>
   <b>
    Movement
   </b>
   :  Each hand moves in a small circle.  They
   <b>
    don't
   </b>
   go up and down.  They both move forward, then out to the side, then back
  toward the body, then in towards each other.
   <br/>
   <b>
    Non-Manual Marker
   </b>
   (Facial expressions and or body language) neutral.
   <br/>
  </p>
